    "(14) captures how the treatment intervention, together with network effects, shifts the outcomes relative to the baseline scenario.",
    "When treatment effects are small in magnitude, the quantities Y t-1 and Y 0 t-1 (as well as I t and I 0 t) are expected to remain sufficiently close.",
    "In this case, the remainder term R t in Eq.",
    "(14) can be ignored.",
    "The smoothness assumption in Theorem 3 is also standard in the literature, see for example Li and Wager (2022b)."
